# Vercel Platform Rules

## Runtime
- Default runtime: Node.js
- Edge runtime requires ADR justification in `docs/adr/`
- Document why Edge is needed and trade-offs

## Feature Flags
- Use Vercel Feature Flags for risky rollouts
- New features that could impact users
- Performance-sensitive changes
- Breaking changes or migrations

## Observability
- Emit observability events on all server actions
- Log start/completion of actions
- Track errors and performance metrics
- Use structured logging
- Integrate with Vercel Observability

## Deployment
- Automatic deployments from `main` branch
- Preview deployments from pull requests
- Environment variables in Vercel dashboard
- Use Vercel defaults unless justified

## Services
- Cron jobs: Use Vercel Cron (configure in `vercel.json`)
- Analytics: Use Vercel Analytics and Speed Insights
